ategory:Discovery Channel people]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:American female models]]\n[[Category:Women television producers]]\n[[Category:Fitness and figure competitors]]\n[[Category:Texas A&M University alumni]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "text_old": "{{Orphan|date=June 2016}}\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name        = Beth Hagendorf\n| image       = Beth Hagendorf at the Del Mar horse races 2013.jpg\n| caption     = Hagendorf at the Del Mar horse races 2013.\n| height           = {{height|ft=5|in=4}}\n| weight           = (Contest) 122 lb <br> (Off-Season) 117 lb\n| alma_mater = Texas A&M University\n| occupation  = Actress, TV Producer\n| years_active  = 2012 - present\n| website = {{URL|http://Beth.tv/}}\n}}\n\n'''Beth Nicole Hagendorf''' is an American [[actress]], [[television producer]], and [[television host]]. She starred on [[Discovery Channel]]\u2019s TV series \"Fire in the Hole.\" Hagendorf was the host for TV show \"Drifting with The All Stars\" on  [[Velocity (TV channel)]]. She is also known for her bikini contests in [[bodybuilding]] and her appearances in [[Flex Magazine]].\n\n==Early life==\nBeth Hagendorf was raised on a 6,000-acre cattle ranch, Tait Ranch, in Columbus, Texas. She grew up a sporty [[tomboy]], riding [[4-wheeler]]s, and running wild on the ranch.<ref name=\"\u201cDiscovery.com\">[http://www.discovery.com/tv-shows/fire-in-the-hole/bios/beth-hagendorf/ Discovery.com]</ref> Hagendorf's mother died at the age of 49 after battling cancer for seven brave years.<ref>[http://www.coloradocountycitizen.com/news/obituaries/article_bcaf40cf-fa6a-5048-b029-a334219a2f3f.html Colorado Cnty Citizen]</ref>  Hagendorf graduated from [[Texas A&M University]] in 3 years with a [[Bachelor of Science]] in [[Sociology]] and minor in [[Psychology]].<ref name=\"Hagendorf Interview\">[http://www.flexonline.com/general-news/bikini-model-search-july-2012-winner-beth-hagendorf Hagendorf Interview] Flex Magazine</ref>\n\n==Career==\nIn 2011, she moved to [[La Jolla]] [[California]] and entered her first [[National Physique Committee|NPC]] contest.<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/name/nm5576123/ Bio] IMDB.com</ref><ref>[http://lindsayproductions.com/scoresheets/11ex/Excalibur_11__Bikini.pdf Open Bikini C class] NPC Results</ref> That year on New Year's Eve she was scouted by a model management company at a La Jolla restaurant and that began her modeling career.<ref name=\"Avoir Magazine\">[http://www.editionduo.com/publication/?i=121443&p=5 Avoir Magazine]</ref> May 12, 2012, Hagendorf earned her Bikini Champion title in the [[International Natural Bodybuilding Association|INBA]].<ref name=\"INBA\">[http://archive.aweber.com/inba/PXwRE/h/INBA_May_June_Events_World.htm# Contest Results] INBA.com</ref> In July 2012, Hagendorf won [[Flex Magazine]] [[bikini model]] search.<ref name=\"Hagendorf Interview\"/><ref>[http://www.flexonline.com/general-news/july-2012-flex-bikini-model-search-winners-have-been-announced Model Search Results] Flex Magazine</ref>  In 2012, Hagendorf began her acting career when cast in a straight-to-video horror film, \"Four Square,\" and was the TV show host of \"The Talk of San Diego.\"<ref name=\"Hagendorf Filmography\">[https://www.imdb.com/name/nm5576123/ Hagendorf Filmography] IMDB.com</ref>   In late 2013, she was cast to host the TV show \"Drifting with The All Stars.\" <ref name =\"Hagendorf Filmography\"/> [[Discovery Channel]]'s TV series \"Fire in the Hole\" followed an [[explosives]] company, Hagendorf is affiliated with.<ref name =\"Hagendorf Filmography\"/><ref>[http://www.discovery.com/tv-shows/fire-in-the-hole/about/ About Fire in the Hole]  Discovery.com</ref> She has now recreated an explosives television series in development.\n\n==Filmography <ref name =\"Hagendorf Filmography\"/>==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ Television\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2012\n| The T